Wasps and bees,

05:49.500 --> 05:51.667
members of the same
insect family,

05:51.669 --> 05:53.502
both with two pairs
of wings,

05:53.504 --> 05:55.004
both with stingers.

05:55.006 --> 05:58.309
Can anyone tell me any
differences between them?

06:03.581 --> 06:05.049
Mr. Breyer?

06:07.018 --> 06:09.852
Uh, well, um,
bees are pollinators,

06:09.854 --> 06:11.453
and wasps
are predators.

06:11.455 --> 06:14.089
Good, good. Anybody else?

06:14.091 --> 06:16.892
And wasps are more aggressive,
more dangerous.

06:16.894 --> 06:19.094
One species,
the Polistes sulcifer,

06:19.096 --> 06:21.063
is what's called
a brood parasite,

06:21.065 --> 06:23.299
they've lost the ability
to make nests,

06:23.301 --> 06:24.800
so they use brute force

06:24.802 --> 06:27.370
to make other wasp species
raise their young.

06:27.372 --> 06:29.905
And they make them feed
their babies things

06:29.907 --> 06:31.707
like beetle larvae
and maggots.

06:31.709 --> 06:34.377
Bro, why are you always
talking about maggots?

06:34.379 --> 06:36.879
- You must be one.
- [ALL LAUGH]

06:36.881 --> 06:38.280
