You're one of the only
people in the world

37:21.526 --> 37:24.292
that knows how
special I am.

37:24.294 --> 37:26.662
But someday...

37:26.664 --> 37:28.666
they will all know.

37:31.636 --> 37:35.905
[SOBBING] My mom told
me not to talk to you.

37:35.907 --> 37:38.641
[SIGHS]
I'm gonna take care of that.

37:38.643 --> 37:40.545
[CRYING]

37:53.825 --> 37:55.925
ERIKA:
Have good one, Gary.

37:55.927 --> 37:57.328
[DOOR CLOSES,
BELL JINGLES]

37:58.429 --> 37:59.931
[REGISTER DINGS]

38:15.746 --> 38:17.181
[DOOR CLOSES,
BELL JINGLES]

38:19.817 --> 38:21.719
[PAPER RUSTLING]

38:23.254 --> 38:25.156
[PLATES CLINKING]

38:40.671 --> 38:42.573
[♪♪♪]

38:51.816 --> 38:53.716
Hey, who's messing
with me?

38:53.718 --> 38:55.219
[LIGHTS HUM]

38:57.321 --> 38:58.823
Is that you, Gary?

39:01.392 --> 39:03.559
[CLICKING]

39:03.561 --> 39:05.496
[♪♪♪]

39:13.871 --> 39:15.773
- [GLASS BREAKS]
- [SCREAMS]

39:20.345 --> 39:23.247
[GROANING, SOBBING]

39:29.120 --> 39:31.055
[GROANING]

39:48.039 --> 39:50.105
[CRYING, GASPING]

39:50.107 --> 39:52.009
[♪♪♪]

39:58.649 --> 40:00.584
[LIGHTS CLICKING, HUMMING]

40:16.435 --> 40:17.967
[SCREAMS]
Get out of here!

40:17.969 --> 40:20.304
[OBJECTS BREAKING, CLATTERING]

40:24.108 --> 40:26.477
- [BAT CLATTERING]
- [SOBBING] Leave me alone!

40:29.981 --> 40:32.449
- [SOBBING]
- [DOOR CLICKS, OPENS]

40:32.451 --> 40:34.183
[DOOR SLAMS, LOCK RATTLES]

40:34.185 --> 40:36.020
[BOXES CRASHING, THUDDING]

40:37.989 --> 40:39.890
[KNOCKING]

40:46.163 --> 40:48.065
[ELECTRONIC FEEDBACK]

40:52.503 --> 40:54.138
[SOBBING]

41:04.115 --> 41:05.549
- [CRASHING]
- [SCREAMS]

41:19.498 --> 41:20.996
[PLOPPING]

41:20.998 --> 41:22.297
Is he awake?

41:22.299 --> 41:24.166
I called up two times
already,

41:24.168 --> 41:25.768
I heard him
walking around.

41:25.770 --> 41:28.137
Should somebody go
get him, I mean...

41:28.139 --> 41:30.139
Morning.

41:30.141 --> 41:31.940
Hey, bud.

41:31.942 --> 41:34.710
Uh, you know you're
going to be late for school.

41:34.712 --> 41:38.847
Yeah, I know, I was just
up in my room... thinking.

41:38.849 --> 41:40.419
Thinking about what?

41:42.653 --> 41:44.219
Just about everything.

41:44.221 --> 41:47.191
And, uh,
it's totally cool.

41:49.593 --> 41:51.994
I feel good.

41:51.996 --> 41:53.496
- [CHUCKLES]
- [SCOFFS]

41:53.498 --> 41:55.498
I'm glad you
feel that way, buddy.

41:55.500 --> 41:56.665
Me too.

41:56.667 --> 41:58.535
Why don't you grab
a seat?

41:58.537 --> 42:00.669
Ten minutes late never
killed anyone.

42:00.671 --> 42:02.807
[SHUTTER CLICKS]

42:05.709 --> 42:10.312
You say she hasn't responded
to any calls or texts?

42:10.314 --> 42:12.314
That's correct.

42:12.316 --> 42:14.417
This was the last place
she was seen.

42:14.419 --> 42:17.353
[SHUTTER CLICKS]

42:17.355 --> 42:19.588
Doesn't look like
a robbery.

42:19.590 --> 42:21.526
[♪♪♪]

42:29.534 --> 42:30.935
Good, God.

42:32.370 --> 42:35.170
Have you talked
to her daughter?

42:35.172 --> 42:37.639
She's a mess right now.

42:37.641 --> 42:39.808
Scared shitless.

42:39.810 --> 42:41.679
I barely got two words
out of her.

42:43.314 --> 42:44.583
SHERIFF:
What is that?

42:52.557 --> 42:54.459
[BREATHES]

42:58.729 --> 43:01.397
MERILEE: So I know this
is kind of strange,

43:01.399 --> 43:03.966
I'm your aunt,
and I'm also your counselor,

43:03.968 --> 43:06.301
but I'm the only one
the district's got,

43:06.303 --> 43:07.805
so you are stuck with me.

43:09.073 --> 43:10.772
So Brandon,
your mom tells me

43:10.774 --> 43:13.208
that you've been having
some issues lately

43:13.210 --> 43:14.812
about being adopted.

43:16.414 --> 43:17.946
Nothing bad,

43:17.948 --> 43:19.281
- only good ones.
- Really?

43:19.283 --> 43:21.650
How so?

43:21.652 --> 43:23.886
I've realized I'm special.

43:23.888 --> 43:27.656
Because my real parents aren't
from a stupid place like here.

43:27.658 --> 43:31.226
You don't think of you mom
and dad as your real parents?

43:31.228 --> 43:33.962
I do, but I just know
I'm something else.

43:33.964 --> 43:35.634
Something superior.

43:39.970 --> 43:41.270
Brandon,

43:41.272 --> 43:43.005
do you feel bad

43:43.007 --> 43:45.876
about what you did to Caitlyn?

43:48.346 --> 43:50.112
You know,

43:50.114 --> 43:51.780
sometimes

43:51.782 --> 43:53.815
when bad things
happen to people,

43:53.817 --> 43:55.554
it's for a good reason.

43:58.956 --> 44:01.357
Brandon,
part of my job

44:01.359 --> 44:02.925
is to update the school,

44:02.927 --> 44:05.227
and to update your mom
on your progress,

44:05.229 --> 44:07.729
and to let them know
if you are showing any

44:07.731 --> 44:09.499
growth or remorse,
and I...-

44:09.501 --> 44:14.305
I can't take it easy on you
because you're my family.

44:16.006 --> 44:18.641
I'm giving you an opportunity
to talk to me,

44:18.643 --> 44:21.176
I'm supposed to update
the sheriff tomorrow,

44:21.178 --> 44:23.312
and I have to be
honest with him.

44:23.314 --> 44:25.216
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

44:26.551 --> 44:28.486
[VOICES SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY]

44:35.393 --> 44:37.560
Yeah, my buddy said
the diner was just...

44:37.562 --> 44:40.729
[GROANS] Was just wrecked.
And the waitress Erika

44:40.731 --> 44:42.398
was gone.
It's been 24 hours.

44:42.400 --> 44:45.234
Wow, Kyle, you think
your son could have done it?

44:45.236 --> 44:46.235
- [SCOFFS]
- [SIGHS]

44:46.237 --> 44:47.537
- Dude!
- What?

44:47.539 --> 44:49.339
He crushed
her daughter's hand.

44:49.341 --> 44:51.407
That's not funny
right now, okay?

44:51.409 --> 44:53.543
- Okay, I'm sorry.
- So, uh...

44:53.545 --> 44:55.345
What's gonna happen
with all that?

44:55.347 --> 44:57.580
I don't know.
He got suspended for a few days,

44:57.582 --> 45:00.048
and I'm sure I'm gonna get
a call from some lawyer

45:00.050 --> 45:02.017
telling me my son's
a monster, which...

45:02.019 --> 45:03.686
I don't even know anymore.
Maybe he is.

45:03.688 --> 45:05.787
They're all monsters.
I'm going home.

45:05.789 --> 45:07.590
Come on. One more.

45:07.592 --> 45:09.791
- One more. Come on.
- No, no. I gotta get home,

45:09.793 --> 45:11.527
- or Merilee's gonna kill me.
- I'll drive you.

45:11.529 --> 45:13.262
It's just a few miles
down the road.

45:13.264 --> 45:15.899
- No, hang. I'll drive.
- Mommy, I'm okay.

45:18.168 --> 45:19.404
Brandon!

45:22.574 --> 45:24.576
I'm home.
I got us sesame chicken.

45:28.045 --> 45:29.113
Brandon?

45:54.739 --> 45:56.708
[ELECTRICITY SIZZLES,
GLASS SHAKES]

45:58.410 --> 45:59.344
What?

46:14.659 --> 46:16.193
[SIGHS]

46:17.828 --> 46:19.495
- [LIGHTS CLICK ON]
- [COMPUTER BEEPS]

46:19.497 --> 46:22.032
COMPUTER:
<i>Alert. Motion, backyard.</i>

46:23.668 --> 46:24.703
What?

46:34.579 --> 46:35.513
[LIGHTS CLICK OFF]

46:41.653 --> 46:42.853
- [KNOCKS ON DOOR]
- [GASPS]

46:46.624 --> 46:47.991
[WHISPERS]
Who the hell?

46:49.527 --> 46:50.994
[KNOCKING CONTINUES]

47:04.743 --> 47:07.343
- Hey.
- Brandon, Jesus.

47:07.345 --> 47:09.244
What are you doing here?

47:09.246 --> 47:11.146
I need to talk to you.

47:11.148 --> 47:14.249
I know it's late,
but I promise I won't take long.

47:14.251 --> 47:15.884
Okay. Fine.

47:15.886 --> 47:18.053
Back in your office,
you mentioned something about

47:18.055 --> 47:20.055
talking to
the sheriff tomorrow?

47:20.057 --> 47:21.890
Mm-hmm.
That's right.

47:21.892 --> 47:24.192
Yeah, the thing is...

47:24.194 --> 47:27.363
that can't happen, ever.

47:27.365 --> 47:30.232
It's just not good for anyone.

47:30.234 --> 47:33.469
Not for me,
not for my parents,

47:33.471 --> 47:37.340
and it's really,
really not good for you.

47:37.342 --> 47:38.942
At all.

47:42.747 --> 47:45.313
Brandon,
listen to me, okay?

47:45.315 --> 47:46.915
I have to do my job.

47:46.917 --> 47:49.752
And to be honest, you showing up
at my house this late

47:49.754 --> 47:51.387
is very inappropriate.

47:51.389 --> 47:53.491
I'm gonna need you
to go home now, okay?

47:54.893 --> 47:56.291
Okay.

47:56.293 --> 47:57.729
I'll walk back.

48:00.130 --> 48:01.900
Okay, sweetie.
Be safe.

48:02.901 --> 48:04.067
You too.

48:11.975 --> 48:13.275
[COMPUTER BEEPS]

48:13.277 --> 48:15.143
COMPUTER:
<i>Alert. Motion, backyard.</i>

48:15.145 --> 48:17.880
[MURMURS]
What the hell? Seriously?

48:17.882 --> 48:19.549
[COMPUTER BEEPS]
COMPUTER: <i>Alert.</i>

48:19.551 --> 48:21.318
- <i>Motion, backyard.</i>
- [SIGHS]

48:25.055 --> 48:26.891
[IN NORMAL VOICE]
Brandon, is that you?

48:30.395 --> 48:32.795
This is so annoying.

48:32.797 --> 48:34.430
- [LIGHT CLICKS]
- [COMPUTER BEEPING]

48:34.432 --> 48:37.600
COMPUTER:
<i>Alert. Alert. Alert.</i>

48:37.602 --> 48:40.235
- <i>Motion, backyard.</i>
- Ugh, great.

48:40.237 --> 48:42.574
The whole freaking house
is falling apart.

48:51.114 --> 48:53.283
[PHONE KEYBOARD CLACKING]

49:02.327 --> 49:04.462
[♪♪♪]

49:08.700 --> 49:09.734
[PHONE CHIME WHOOSHES]

49:24.482 --> 49:25.517
[PHONE LOCK CLICKS]

49:46.169 --> 49:48.238
- [DOOR CLOSES]
- [KEYS RUSTLE]

49:55.413 --> 49:56.881
[COUGHS SOFTLY]

50:10.227 --> 50:11.462
[SIGHS]

50:23.975 --> 50:26.176
[♪♪♪]

50:34.018 --> 50:35.053
[SOFT WHOOSH]

50:36.086 --> 50:37.187
Oh, shit.

50:39.524 --> 50:41.426
[♪♪♪]

50:46.196 --> 50:47.097
[GASPS]

50:48.433 --> 50:51.033
Brandon? What the fuck
are you doing?

50:51.035 --> 50:53.234
Aunt Merilee was helping me
with my homework.

50:53.236 --> 50:54.604
No, what the fuck
are you doing in my closet

50:54.606 --> 50:56.439
- wearing this creepy mask?
- It's not creepy.

50:56.441 --> 50:58.810
You scared the shit out of me,
weirdo! I'm taking you home.

51:01.746 --> 51:04.245
- This is fucking insane, man.
- I didn't do anything.

51:04.247 --> 51:05.715
Are you gonna
tell my parents?

51:05.717 --> 51:07.284
You're lucky
if that's all I do!

51:09.921 --> 51:11.286
Get in the truck.

51:11.288 --> 51:12.857
You shouldn't tell my parents.

51:18.096 --> 51:19.931
Brandon, get in the truck!

51:22.333 --> 51:23.334
[ZAPS]

51:26.771 --> 51:28.271
[COUGHS]

51:33.578 --> 51:35.245
[PANTING]

51:37.949 --> 51:39.214
[ELECTRICITY CRACKLES]

51:39.216 --> 51:40.315
Shit.

51:40.317 --> 51:41.419
[GRUNTS]

51:48.726 --> 51:50.862
[PANTING]
What the fuck!

51:52.162 --> 51:53.464
[♪♪♪]

52:07.679 --> 52:08.844
[BRAKES SQUEAL]

52:08.846 --> 52:09.747
Holy sh...

52:11.516 --> 52:12.583
[PAINED GROAN]

52:13.985 --> 52:15.017
What the...?

52:15.019 --> 52:16.652
[ENGINE SPUTTERS]

52:16.654 --> 52:17.887
[BRAKES SQUEAL]

52:17.889 --> 52:19.021
No. Come on, come on.

52:19.023 --> 52:20.523
- No, no, no.
- [ENGINE SPUTTERING]

52:20.525 --> 52:21.857
Come on, come on, come on.

52:21.859 --> 52:23.559
Ah, man!

52:23.561 --> 52:25.394
Come on, not now!

52:25.396 --> 52:27.530
Just... Come on!

52:27.532 --> 52:29.865
Come on, come on, come on!

52:29.867 --> 52:31.434
Come on!

52:31.436 --> 52:33.469
[SPUTTERING CONTINUES]

52:33.471 --> 52:35.337
Come on!

52:35.339 --> 52:36.639
Damn it.

52:36.641 --> 52:39.442
Come on, come on, come on.
Come on!

52:39.444 --> 52:41.209
Stupid piece of shit!

52:41.211 --> 52:43.347
[TURN SIGNAL CLICKING]

52:45.016 --> 52:47.149
Oh, shit. Okay.

52:47.151 --> 52:49.987
Okay, it's time to go.
Come on!

52:52.857 --> 52:54.490
Nope. Mm-mmm.

52:54.492 --> 52:56.859
No, no, no.

52:56.861 --> 52:58.728
- [ENGINE SPUTTERS]
- Come on!

52:58.730 --> 53:00.930
Get out of here!
Gotta go!

53:00.932 --> 53:03.201
Let's go! Come on!

53:06.037 --> 53:07.304
[GROANS]

53:10.875 --> 53:12.174
Uh...

53:12.176 --> 53:13.409
Okay.

53:13.411 --> 53:15.377
Um... uh...

53:15.379 --> 53:17.548
This is, uh, really bad.

53:21.519 --> 53:23.686
[CAR CREAKS]

53:23.688 --> 53:25.788
What the... What the fuck!
No, stop, stop!

53:25.790 --> 53:27.857
Come on, put me down!
Hey, man, stop!

53:27.859 --> 53:31.095
Oh, shit! Oh, fuck.
No, no. Fuck, fuck, fuck!

53:32.830 --> 53:35.397
Oh, shit! Oh, God!

53:35.399 --> 53:36.866
Goddamn it!

53:36.868 --> 53:38.703
God! Fuck!

53:40.738 --> 53:41.939
[SCREAMS]

53:54.018 --> 53:55.720
[GROANS]

53:58.356 --> 54:00.290
[GAGGING]

54:05.630 --> 54:07.331
[CHOKING, HACKING]

54:11.669 --> 54:14.472
[♪♪♪]

55:02.687 --> 55:05.187
Hi, Merilee. I know
I'm leaving a lot of messages.

55:05.189 --> 55:07.890
It's after 10 now, and we still
haven't seen him, so...

55:07.892 --> 55:09.792
Did she say anything
to him at school?

55:09.794 --> 55:12.027
Maybe he said something
to you at school or...

55:12.029 --> 55:14.630
- Like he got a ride home or...
- Shut up!

55:14.632 --> 55:16.532
...where he
to go after school.

55:16.534 --> 55:19.702
I'm rambling
because I'm freaking out,

55:19.704 --> 55:22.404
so just please call me back.
Thank you, honey.

55:22.406 --> 55:25.543
- Would you please stop?
- I didn't say anything.

55:27.812 --> 55:29.080
Oh, my God, baby!

55:30.314 --> 55:32.414
Where have you been?

55:32.416 --> 55:35.150
Where were you?
What happened to your shirt?

55:35.152 --> 55:36.685
I was playing soccer.

55:36.687 --> 55:38.888
You've been playing soccer
this whole time?

55:38.890 --> 55:40.856
Well, after school,

55:40.858 --> 55:43.692
Royce and them asked me
if I wanted to play.

55:43.694 --> 55:46.495
And as soon as
the game started, they were...

55:46.497 --> 55:49.366
They were tripping me
and pushing me to the ground,

55:49.368 --> 55:52.635
and, you know,
they were all laughing

55:52.637 --> 55:54.536
because my shirt got ripped.

55:54.538 --> 55:57.473
I just decided I'd walk
all the way home.

55:57.475 --> 55:59.842
I know I should have called.

55:59.844 --> 56:01.677
- Yes.
- Actually, I'm...

56:01.679 --> 56:03.812
I'm just really tired.
I'm gonna go to bed.

56:03.814 --> 56:05.481
Okay, well,
let me take this...

56:05.483 --> 56:07.318
No. No.

56:08.619 --> 56:10.387
Don't worry about it.

56:10.389 --> 56:11.555
It's fine.

56:17.295 --> 56:19.297
I'll come up
in a couple minutes.

56:22.600 --> 56:24.133
- He's lying.
- Yeah, obviously.

56:24.135 --> 56:26.635
If we don't do something,
this is gonna get worse.

56:26.637 --> 56:27.970
- What the fuck do we do?
- I don't know.

56:27.972 --> 56:29.638
Maybe we need
to talk to somebody.

56:29.640 --> 56:31.206
- He needs a specialist.
- What?

56:31.208 --> 56:32.908
- And say what to them?
- I don't know.

56:32.910 --> 56:34.377
"Hello, this is our son.

56:34.379 --> 56:36.278
We found him in a fucking
spaceship in the woods.

56:36.280 --> 56:37.746
Now what?"
No, we should have

56:37.748 --> 56:40.051
done something a long
time ago. This is on us.

56:45.790 --> 56:46.924
[SIGHING]

56:48.926 --> 56:51.829
KYLE: <i>Maybe this time,
we get lucky and make a baby?</i>

56:55.933 --> 56:57.168
[GROANS]

57:06.644 --> 57:08.243
TORI:
<i>Just shut up and kiss me.</i>

57:08.245 --> 57:09.244
[SCREAMS]

57:09.246 --> 57:12.049
[♪♪♪]

57:21.826 --> 57:24.427
TORI: <i>There's, like,
a light in the woods.</i>

57:24.429 --> 57:25.397
What the...?

57:28.666 --> 57:30.001
Tori?

57:32.303 --> 57:33.671
Tori?

57:47.685 --> 57:48.986
[VOICE ECHOING]
Tori?

57:57.094 --> 57:58.363
Tori?

58:03.868 --> 58:04.802
Hey, baby.

58:06.170 --> 58:07.071
What are you doing?

58:10.107 --> 58:12.076
[BABY CRYING FAINTLY]

58:14.712 --> 58:16.047
[VOICE ECHOING]
It's a boy.

58:25.890 --> 58:29.894
Oh, we've tried for so long
to have a baby, and he's here.

58:33.931 --> 58:36.634
He's here. A gift.

58:43.841 --> 58:46.809
[♪♪♪]

58:46.811 --> 58:48.879
[TORI & BABY LAUGH EERILY]

58:54.752 --> 58:56.685
[CELL PHONE RINGING]

58:56.687 --> 58:58.488
[PANTING]

58:58.490 --> 59:00.322
Hello?

59:00.324 --> 59:02.126
- Oh, God.
- Hey, hey. Huh?

59:03.060 --> 59:04.695
[GROANING]

59:05.896 --> 59:07.098
Mer.

59:13.070 --> 59:14.603
You all right?

59:14.605 --> 59:16.872
No. They won't let me see him
because his...

59:16.874 --> 59:20.577
They said that his face
is too mangled.

59:20.579 --> 59:22.878
Do they know what happened?

59:22.880 --> 59:25.482
They were...
They found him on Route 18.

59:25.484 --> 59:28.485
They think that he swerved
to not hit a deer, and...

59:28.487 --> 59:30.553
They're doing
the toxicology

59:30.555 --> 59:32.388
to make sure
that he wasn't drinking.

59:32.390 --> 59:33.889
Was he drinking?

59:33.891 --> 59:36.959
No, he just had
like two or three drinks of...

59:36.961 --> 59:38.363
I mean,
I wasn't counting.

59:40.898 --> 59:42.398
How's Brandon?

59:42.400 --> 59:44.334
He's okay.
We didn't tell him anything.

59:44.336 --> 59:46.068
No, but did
he get home okay?

59:46.070 --> 59:47.803
- Yes, he did.
- Okay.

59:47.805 --> 59:49.271
Thank God. Thank God.

59:49.273 --> 59:52.375
He came over and I didn't
remember when he left,

59:52.377 --> 59:54.178
so I'm just glad
that he's okay.

59:55.480 --> 59:56.914
He left you?

01:00:00.651 --> 01:00:02.820
[♪♪♪]

01:00:09.994 --> 01:00:11.262
Morning, baby.

01:00:16.200 --> 01:00:17.266
Um...

01:00:17.268 --> 01:00:18.867
[SNIFFS]

01:00:18.869 --> 01:00:21.371
There's something that
we need to discuss with you,

01:00:21.373 --> 01:00:24.576
and it's probably
gonna be hard to hear.

01:00:26.444 --> 01:00:28.677
Last night,
your Uncle Noah...

01:00:28.679 --> 01:00:30.181
[SIGHS]

01:00:32.783 --> 01:00:34.318
He died last night.

01:00:36.887 --> 01:00:37.855
Okay.

01:00:41.692 --> 01:00:43.725
Brandon,
do you understand?

01:00:43.727 --> 01:00:47.332
Your Uncle Noah passed away.
He's gone.

01:00:51.436 --> 01:00:53.603
I feel like you want me to cry
or something.

01:00:53.605 --> 01:00:56.205
Do you wanna cry?

01:00:56.207 --> 01:00:59.678
Brandon, we know you were
at Aunt Merilee's last night.

01:01:03.847 --> 01:01:06.281
Honey, I'm your mom.

01:01:06.283 --> 01:01:08.317
I will always defend you.

01:01:08.319 --> 01:01:11.521
But if you know something
about what happened to Noah,

01:01:11.523 --> 01:01:12.890
you need to tell us.

01:01:19.830 --> 01:01:22.030
I don't know
what happened to him.

01:01:22.032 --> 01:01:24.567
But I would never
hurt Uncle Noah.

01:01:24.569 --> 01:01:25.936
I love him.

01:01:27.339 --> 01:01:29.771
That is bullshit.
He is fucking lying!

01:01:29.773 --> 01:01:30.872
Kyle.

01:01:30.874 --> 01:01:32.408
Look, we know you were there.

01:01:32.410 --> 01:01:34.042
What else are you
lying to us about?

01:01:34.044 --> 01:01:35.744
Can you calm down?

01:01:35.746 --> 01:01:37.680
- Were you in Caitlyn's bedroom?
- He was camping with us.

01:01:37.682 --> 01:01:39.915
Where were you Wednesday
when Caitlyn's mom went missing?

01:01:39.917 --> 01:01:42.284
- This is not helping!
- He is lying to our faces!

01:01:42.286 --> 01:01:44.721
- I'm gonna go upstairs.
- You're what...

01:01:44.723 --> 01:01:46.855
No, you're not.
You are not going anywhere

01:01:46.857 --> 01:01:48.257
until we get all this
on the table.

01:01:48.259 --> 01:01:49.992
- Kyle, I will handle it!
- No, no, no.

01:01:49.994 --> 01:01:51.327
Did you hurt Noah?

01:01:51.329 --> 01:01:52.528
What did you do to him!

01:01:52.530 --> 01:01:54.062
He was my friend,
and you just...

01:01:54.064 --> 01:01:55.197
Leave me alone!

01:01:55.199 --> 01:01:56.133
[GRUNTS]

01:01:58.168 --> 01:02:00.104
[BOTH PANTING]

01:02:01.772 --> 01:02:03.073
[SOFTLY]
Brandon.

01:02:06.611 --> 01:02:08.578
You need to go to your room.

01:02:08.580 --> 01:02:10.178
Just go to your room.

01:02:10.180 --> 01:02:11.549
[WHISPERS]
Are you all right?

01:02:14.519 --> 01:02:16.084
Honey?

01:02:16.086 --> 01:02:18.220
He's hiding that shirt
for some reason.

01:02:18.222 --> 01:02:19.788
Honey.

01:02:19.790 --> 01:02:21.925
[SHOWER RUNNING]

01:02:44.014 --> 01:02:46.216
[SHOWER CREAKS, STOPS]

01:02:51.656 --> 01:02:54.793
[♪♪♪]

01:02:58.262 --> 01:02:59.364
Shit.

01:03:05.169 --> 01:03:06.303
BRANDON:
Dad?

01:03:08.440 --> 01:03:09.641
Hey, bud.

01:03:11.509 --> 01:03:13.277
I wanted to apologize.

01:03:15.846 --> 01:03:18.115
We've been going through
a lot lately, and...

01:03:19.651 --> 01:03:22.052
I shouldn't have said
what I said to you.

01:03:23.388 --> 01:03:24.321
Okay.

01:03:26.358 --> 01:03:27.991
- Come here, get in here.
- What? What?

01:03:30.829 --> 01:03:32.861
- It's right there.
- That could be anything.

01:03:32.863 --> 01:03:35.498
No. That is why he was hiding
this from us last night.

01:03:35.500 --> 01:03:38.166
- That is Noah's blood.
- How?

01:03:38.168 --> 01:03:40.670
How could Brandon
have killed Noah

01:03:40.672 --> 01:03:42.372
and then made it look
like a car accident?

01:03:42.374 --> 01:03:43.972
Who knows what kind
of weird shit he could do?

01:03:43.974 --> 01:03:47.309
Noah was drunk
and wrecked the car

01:03:47.311 --> 01:03:49.746
- because you let him drive.
- No, that is not what...

01:03:49.748 --> 01:03:52.314
And now you are trying
to take out your guilt

01:03:52.316 --> 01:03:54.384
- on our 12-year-old son.
- Babe...

01:03:54.386 --> 01:03:59.321
You are making
a hard situation impossible.

01:03:59.323 --> 01:04:01.123
Babe, we've got
to do something.

01:04:01.125 --> 01:04:03.359
If we don't, more people
are gonna get hurt.

01:04:03.361 --> 01:04:06.294
More people will die.
You gotta be with me on this.

01:04:06.296 --> 01:04:08.731
I will never
turn against our son.

01:04:08.733 --> 01:04:10.232
He's not our son!

01:04:10.234 --> 01:04:12.668
He is some thing
we found in the woods.

01:04:12.670 --> 01:04:15.203
How fucking dare
you say that to me.

01:04:15.205 --> 01:04:16.839
- How dare you.
- Babe!

01:04:16.841 --> 01:04:18.206
How can you
fucking say that to me?

01:04:18.208 --> 01:04:20.476
Babe. Come on,
he's killing us.

01:04:20.478 --> 01:04:22.845
REPORTER: <i>We now turn to
more somber news tonight</i>

01:04:22.847 --> 01:04:25.848
<i>as authorities are reaching out
to the public for information</i>

01:04:25.850 --> 01:04:29.017
<i>in their search for missing
Darbo's waitress, Erika Connor,</i>

01:04:29.019 --> 01:04:33.456
<i>who was last seen at the iconic
Route 74 diner Wednesday.</i>

01:04:33.458 --> 01:04:35.725
<i>Anyone with information
about her whereabouts</i>

01:04:35.727 --> 01:04:38.093
<i>is strongly urged
to contact police officials...</i>

01:04:38.095 --> 01:04:39.764
[INDISTINCT RADIO CHATTER]

01:04:50.909 --> 01:04:53.177
[♪♪♪]

01:05:35.954 --> 01:05:38.021
[SIGHING]

01:05:45.996 --> 01:05:47.832
[SIGHS]

01:05:51.703 --> 01:05:52.704
You okay?

01:05:55.340 --> 01:05:57.509
[♪♪♪]

01:06:01.078 --> 01:06:02.612
I think I'm gonna take him...

01:06:02.614 --> 01:06:05.247
I'm gonna take him away
this weekend.

01:06:05.249 --> 01:06:07.917
Just the two of us.

01:06:07.919 --> 01:06:10.820
Take him out to Drywood.

01:06:10.822 --> 01:06:12.824
Be his dad.

01:06:14.826 --> 01:06:16.861
Let him know I love him.

01:06:35.346 --> 01:06:37.212
Here, don't forget these.

01:06:37.214 --> 01:06:40.148
- Just wear them for me.
- Okay.

01:06:40.150 --> 01:06:41.586
Come here.

01:06:48.993 --> 01:06:50.862
You'll always be
my baby boy.

01:06:54.365 --> 01:06:56.701
Even though
you're getting so tall.

01:06:58.201 --> 01:06:59.704
Go have fun
with your dad, okay?

01:07:02.340 --> 01:07:03.374
All right.

01:07:05.910 --> 01:07:07.545
- Seat belt.
- Right.

01:07:11.214 --> 01:07:12.717
See you Sunday.

01:07:15.185 --> 01:07:16.688
[ENGINE STARTS]

01:07:24.529 --> 01:07:28.298
[♪♪♪]

01:08:15.747 --> 01:08:17.212
Afternoon, Tori.

01:08:17.214 --> 01:08:18.180
Hey.

01:08:20.385 --> 01:08:21.953
Your boy around,
by chance?

01:08:23.252 --> 01:08:25.220
Brandon went hunting
with his dad.

01:08:25.221 --> 01:08:27.122
- Hmm.
- Is something wrong?

01:08:27.125 --> 01:08:29.594
Maybe you can answer
a question for me.

01:08:31.328 --> 01:08:32.930
This look familiar to you?

01:08:34.296 --> 01:08:36.866
Some kind of signature
left at the spots

01:08:36.868 --> 01:08:40.102
where both Erika
went missing and Noah died.

01:08:40.104 --> 01:08:41.139
No. Mm-mm.

01:08:42.506 --> 01:08:46.542
Doesn't that look
like a "BB," maybe,

01:08:46.544 --> 01:08:48.712
as in "Brandon Breyer"?

01:08:50.113 --> 01:08:51.214
I don't see it.

01:08:54.618 --> 01:08:56.852
Do you mind if I come in,
take a look around?

01:08:56.854 --> 01:08:59.390
I do mind. I think,
actually, you should go.

01:09:00.524 --> 01:09:01.826
All right.

01:09:03.627 --> 01:09:04.895
But you know I'll be back.

01:09:13.970 --> 01:09:15.872
[CAR ENGINE TURNS ON, RECEDES]

01:09:17.809 --> 01:09:20.645
[♪♪♪]

01:09:24.448 --> 01:09:25.716
These are deer tracks.

01:09:29.953 --> 01:09:31.823
[PANTING]

01:09:41.933 --> 01:09:44.202
Looks like there's more
than one set of tracks.

01:09:50.608 --> 01:09:53.008
[GASPING]

01:09:53.010 --> 01:09:54.376
No.

01:09:54.378 --> 01:09:55.613
[LOCK CLICKS]

01:10:06.624 --> 01:10:08.092
[WHIMPERS]

01:10:10.728 --> 01:10:11.629
[GROANS]

01:10:14.332 --> 01:10:16.067
Oh, God.

01:10:26.344 --> 01:10:27.376
[GUNSHOT]

01:10:27.378 --> 01:10:28.844
[BIRDS SQUAWKING]

01:10:28.846 --> 01:10:30.045
[GASPS]

01:10:30.047 --> 01:10:31.783
[PANTING]

01:10:38.689 --> 01:10:41.324
[♪♪♪]

01:10:58.609 --> 01:10:59.644
Brandon?

01:11:01.245 --> 01:11:02.446
Oh, man.

01:11:09.787 --> 01:11:10.788
[WHOOSHES]

01:11:15.927 --> 01:11:18.329
[GASPING]

01:11:23.100 --> 01:11:26.137
[GRUNTS, COUGHS]

01:11:28.906 --> 01:11:29.841
Oh, God.

01:11:32.009 --> 01:11:34.810
No. Please stop.

01:11:34.812 --> 01:11:36.147
Please. Please.

01:11:37.949 --> 01:11:39.050
God... Ah!

01:11:42.720 --> 01:11:44.687
Brandon, please, stop, stop.

01:11:44.689 --> 01:11:47.389
Don't hurt me, okay?
Brandon, please, please.

01:11:47.391 --> 01:11:49.058
Please. Brandon, don't.
Don't.

01:11:49.060 --> 01:11:50.292
I'm sorry.

01:11:50.294 --> 01:11:52.063
[SCREAMING]

01:12:06.310 --> 01:12:07.378
Pick up, pick up.

01:12:09.747 --> 01:12:10.880
[SOBBING]
Kyle.

01:12:10.882 --> 01:12:12.615
Kyle, I'm sorry.
You were right.

01:12:12.617 --> 01:12:14.884
Baby, you were right.
He killed Noah.

01:12:14.886 --> 01:12:16.785
He... Brandon...

01:12:16.787 --> 01:12:19.021
Brandon...
He killed Noah.

01:12:19.023 --> 01:12:20.391
And...

01:12:22.327 --> 01:12:23.728
Kyle?

01:12:26.331 --> 01:12:28.063
BRANDON [ON PHONE]:
<i>Mom.</i>

01:12:28.065 --> 01:12:29.667
[WHISPERS]
Brandon.

01:12:34.138 --> 01:12:35.539
[IN NORMAL VOICE]
Where's Dad?

01:12:37.842 --> 01:12:39.277
<i>He's gone.</i>

01:12:40.878 --> 01:12:42.513
Gone where?

01:12:44.882 --> 01:12:46.417
<i>You know.</i>

01:12:47.518 --> 01:12:49.386
No.

01:12:49.388 --> 01:12:52.888
No, I don't.
I don't know where.

01:12:52.890 --> 01:12:55.126
Where are you?

01:12:56.294 --> 01:12:58.262
I'm home, Mom.

01:13:06.304 --> 01:13:08.306
[DIAL TONE BEEPS]

01:13:13.144 --> 01:13:14.478
Brandon?

01:13:22.354 --> 01:13:24.389
- [THUDS]
- [SCREAMS]

01:13:27.591 --> 01:13:30.795
[♪♪♪]

01:13:37.568 --> 01:13:39.338
[SCREAMING]

01:13:47.979 --> 01:13:50.314
[WHIMPERING]

01:13:54.485 --> 01:13:56.285
Please pick up.
Please pick up.

01:13:56.287 --> 01:13:58.357
[PHONE LINE RINGING]

01:14:00.925 --> 01:14:02.626
[WHISPERS]
Please help me.

01:14:04.595 --> 01:14:05.696
Please...

01:14:06.998 --> 01:14:08.197
OPERATOR [ON PHONE]:
<i>911.</i>

01:14:08.199 --> 01:14:09.800
[SCREAMING]

01:14:13.971 --> 01:14:15.806
[CRIES SOFTLY]

01:14:26.317 --> 01:14:28.019
[GASPING]

01:14:31.622 --> 01:14:33.622
OFFICER [OVER RADIO]: <i>Got a
call from the Breyer residence.</i>

01:14:33.624 --> 01:14:35.492
<i>Tori was screaming,
then the line went dead.</i>

01:14:35.494 --> 01:14:36.658
Shit. I'm on my way.

01:14:36.660 --> 01:14:37.661
[SIREN WAILS]

01:14:57.382 --> 01:14:59.518
- [SIRENS TURN OFF]
- [INDISTINCT RADIO CHATTER]

01:15:02.686 --> 01:15:04.055
What the fuck?

01:15:07.024 --> 01:15:08.025
Yeah.

01:15:10.861 --> 01:15:12.397
[PANTING]

01:15:15.900 --> 01:15:18.901
Tori!
You got the sheriffs here.

01:15:18.903 --> 01:15:20.503
Where are you?

01:15:20.505 --> 01:15:22.840
Come to the sound
of my voice, Tori.

01:15:25.309 --> 01:15:26.642
I'm here, I'm here...

01:15:26.644 --> 01:15:27.745
[SCREAMS]

01:15:30.181 --> 01:15:31.916
Jesus Christ,
what the fuck was that?

01:15:33.250 --> 01:15:34.249
Tori!

01:15:34.251 --> 01:15:36.051
[SOBBING]
I'm here!

01:15:36.053 --> 01:15:37.554
- You're safe now.
- No, no.

01:15:37.556 --> 01:15:38.854
- We got...
- You need to get...

01:15:38.856 --> 01:15:40.722
[SCREAMING]

01:15:40.724 --> 01:15:42.525
Go! Take cover!

01:15:42.527 --> 01:15:43.992
- No, you don't understand...
- Go!

01:15:43.994 --> 01:15:45.894
- Hide! Hide!
- We need to get out.

01:15:45.896 --> 01:15:47.996
Oh, my God.

01:15:47.998 --> 01:15:50.433
[♪♪♪]

01:15:50.435 --> 01:15:51.436
[COCKS GUN]

01:15:53.070 --> 01:15:55.871
Request for backup
at the Breyer residence.

01:15:55.873 --> 01:15:57.474
Immediate help.

01:15:57.476 --> 01:16:00.275
We have a 217 in progress
on Route 9.

01:16:00.277 --> 01:16:02.211
Requesting backup.

01:16:02.213 --> 01:16:04.880
I repeat, I need backup!

01:16:04.882 --> 01:16:06.648
OFFICER [ON RADIO]:
<i>Come in.</i>

01:16:06.650 --> 01:16:07.983
<i>Come in.</i>

01:16:07.985 --> 01:16:10.052
Repeat,
I have a 217 in progress

01:16:10.054 --> 01:16:11.387
at the Breyer residence.

01:16:11.389 --> 01:16:13.423
I need backup immediately!

01:16:13.425 --> 01:16:15.325
[RADIO CRACKLES]

01:16:15.327 --> 01:16:16.495
[DISTORTED]
<i>Officer?</i>

01:16:18.463 --> 01:16:20.297
[ELECTRICITY FIZZLES]

01:16:24.436 --> 01:16:26.768
[HOUSE CREAKING]

01:16:26.770 --> 01:16:27.838
[PANTING SOFTLY]

01:16:46.056 --> 01:16:48.657
If anyone can read me,
I have eyes on the suspect.

01:16:48.659 --> 01:16:49.793
He's outside.

01:16:53.898 --> 01:16:55.864
- [FAINT THUMP]
- [MUFFLED YELLS]

01:16:55.866 --> 01:16:56.867
[WHIMPERS]

01:16:58.802 --> 01:17:00.137
[YELLING]

01:17:04.775 --> 01:17:06.041
[SCREAMS]

01:17:06.043 --> 01:17:07.510
- [GASPS]
- [CHOKING]

01:17:07.512 --> 01:17:09.278
- [GURGLING]
- OFFICER [ON RADIO]: <i>Officer?</i>

01:17:09.280 --> 01:17:10.879
<i>Officer Ayres, come in.</i>

01:17:10.881 --> 01:17:12.681
<i>Come in, Officer Ayres.</i>

01:17:12.683 --> 01:17:15.819
<i>Hello?
Officer Ayres, please respond.</i>

01:17:18.889 --> 01:17:20.925
[ELECTRICITY FIZZLING]

01:17:54.693 --> 01:17:56.894
[SOFT PANTING]

01:18:04.168 --> 01:18:05.769
[FLOOR CREAKS]

01:18:09.907 --> 01:18:10.874
[WHOOSHES]

01:18:21.051 --> 01:18:23.053
[♪♪♪]

01:18:28.360 --> 01:18:30.360
[GRUNTS]

01:18:30.362 --> 01:18:31.730
[GROANS]

01:18:34.098 --> 01:18:35.331
The ship.

01:18:35.333 --> 01:18:37.636
It cut him.
It cut him, it cut him.

01:18:39.169 --> 01:18:41.238
[♪♪♪]

01:18:44.709 --> 01:18:46.645
[PANTING, GASPING]

01:19:02.993 --> 01:19:04.128
[BRANDON YELLS]

01:19:10.435 --> 01:19:11.369
Okay.

01:19:15.839 --> 01:19:16.807
[GASPS]

01:19:18.610 --> 01:19:20.878
[SHIP PULSING]

01:19:22.079 --> 01:19:24.783
[YELPS, SOBS]

01:19:28.919 --> 01:19:30.154
Erika.

01:19:45.804 --> 01:19:47.137
Brandon?

01:19:49.306 --> 01:19:50.974
Where are you, baby?

01:19:53.010 --> 01:19:54.811
Brandon?

01:19:54.813 --> 01:19:56.581
Where are you, baby?

01:19:57.782 --> 01:19:59.718
[♪♪♪]

01:20:00.685 --> 01:20:01.786
Brandon?

01:20:10.495 --> 01:20:12.196
[WHISTLES]

01:20:14.031 --> 01:20:15.533
Where are you, baby?

01:20:20.871 --> 01:20:22.574
Brandon.

01:20:23.641 --> 01:20:25.242
[WHISTLES BROKENLY]

01:20:28.178 --> 01:20:29.381
[PANTING]

01:20:46.831 --> 01:20:47.732
Mom?

01:20:49.967 --> 01:20:51.101
Brandon.

01:20:52.035 --> 01:20:53.203
Listen to me.

01:20:54.639 --> 01:20:57.807
I have never
stopped loving you.

01:20:57.809 --> 01:20:59.742
I believe...

01:20:59.744 --> 01:21:01.744
I still believe

01:21:01.746 --> 01:21:04.347
you were a blessing

01:21:04.349 --> 01:21:06.651
that fell to this Earth.

01:21:19.431 --> 01:21:21.497
When we found you,

01:21:21.499 --> 01:21:24.400
you were so tiny and fragile.

01:21:24.402 --> 01:21:28.270
And all we could do
was keep you safe.

01:21:28.272 --> 01:21:30.675
Whatever you've done,

01:21:32.744 --> 01:21:37.682
I know there is good
inside you.

01:21:40.718 --> 01:21:42.819
I want to do good, Mom.

01:21:42.821 --> 01:21:44.254
I do.

01:21:45.723 --> 01:21:47.155
And you will.

01:21:47.157 --> 01:21:48.927
[CRYING]

01:21:52.464 --> 01:21:56.231
[SOBBING]
You will always be...

01:21:56.233 --> 01:21:58.268
[♪♪♪]

01:22:00.505 --> 01:22:02.707
...my baby boy.

01:22:04.709 --> 01:22:05.976
[GASPS]

01:22:10.949 --> 01:22:13.583
Brandon, I'm sorry.
Oh, Brandon.

01:22:13.585 --> 01:22:15.319
- [BRANDON ROARS]
- [TORI SCREAMS]

01:22:17.655 --> 01:22:19.990
[♪♪♪]

01:23:00.665 --> 01:23:03.334
[♪♪♪]

01:23:21.019 --> 01:23:23.220
[WIND RUSHING]

01:23:41.271 --> 01:23:43.372
MAN:
Rescue one, we have rescue...

01:23:43.374 --> 01:23:47.009
[INDISTINCT RADIO CHATTER]

01:23:47.011 --> 01:23:50.346
REPORTER: Breaking news at this hour.
A passenger jet has crashed

01:23:50.348 --> 01:23:52.615
in the small town
of Brightburn, Kansas.

01:23:52.617 --> 01:23:54.517
Details are still coming in,

01:23:54.519 --> 01:23:56.852
but there are believed
to be no survivors

01:23:56.854 --> 01:24:00.121
